The paper proposes a novel memory architecture for neural networks and demonstrates its effectiveness in learning algorithms for problems like sorting and searching. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data structures such as stacks, queues, and priority queues, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves some applications in computer vision, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV).
